narratives.question_text: Indicate the total number of hours per week (outside the classroom) you spent on this course:
Looking back on this course, what is your overall assessment of the course:  What are its strengths and weaknesses, and in what ways might it be improved?
comments: I assume this is for my fall rotation, which was amazing. I ended up writing a paper and submitting it to Lancet, which was beyond my wildest dreams when I started the project!

narratives.question_text: Please evaluate the instructor of this course. What are the instructor's strengths and weaknesses, and in what ways might his or her teaching be improved?
comments: Instructor: Alison Galvani  David Paltiel was my rotation supervisor. I adore him.

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize this course for a fellow student? Would you recommend it to another student? Why or why not?
comments: These are the EMD rotations--so it depends on whom you work with!

This is the research rotation project, done with a faculty member you select on a project you two agree on. It's very flexible and personal. A great chance to try a new method or test working with a certain professor. It's an important part of the program.
